**Query Comparison**:

| Type | Pros | Cons | Use Case |
|------|------|------|----------|
| Method Name | Simple, readable | Limited complexity | Simple queries |
| @Query JPQL | Type-safe, readable | Verbose | Complex business logic |
| Native SQL | Database features | Fragile, not portable | Very complex queries |
| Criteria API | Type-safe, dynamic | Verbose, complex | Dynamic filters |
| QueryDSL | Type-safe, elegant | Setup required | Complex dynamic queries |

Best Practices:
- Use derived query methods for simple queries
- Use @Query with JPQL for better readability
- Use Specifications for dynamic, reusable filters
- Always use @Param for parameter binding (no index positions)
- Use @Modifying with @Transactional for updates/deletes
- Avoid native SQL unless necessary
- Test queries against actual database
